  "prompt": "How do I import my Gmail contacts into Skype?",
  "response": "To import Gmail contacts into Skype, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open Skype and sign in to your account\n\n2. Click on your profile picture or avatar\n\n3. Go to \"Contacts\"\n\n4. Click \"Import contacts\"\n\n5. Select \"Gmail\" from the list of import options\n\n6. You'll be redirected to sign in to your Google account\n\n7. Grant Skype permission to access your contacts\n\n8. Select the contacts you want to import\n\n9. Click \"Import\"\n\nNote: Make sure you're using the same email address for both your Gmail and Skype accounts for the smoothest import process. If you're using the desktop version of Skype, the steps might vary slightly depending on your version.\n\nIf you encounter any issues, you can also:\n- Export your Gmail contacts to a CSV file\n- Manually add contacts in Skype\n- Check that your contacts have Skype accounts",
